r, n = map(int, input().split())
booked = set(int(input()) for _ in range(n))
for i in range(1, r+1):
    if i not in booked:
        print(i)
        break
else:
    print("too late")


This Python solution reads the number of rooms and the number of booked rooms, reads the booked rooms, and then checks each room in order. If it finds a room that is not in the set of booked rooms, it prints that room number and stops. If it goes through all the rooms without finding an unbooked room, it prints "too late".

The solution is efficient because it uses a set to check if a room is booked in constant time, and it only needs to read the booked rooms once.
